Key Match Events: The Twins fell 6-2 to the Baltimore Orioles Sunday afternoon at Target Field in Minneapolis in their final game of the season.
Carlos Santana hit his team-leading 23rd home run in the second inning.
DaShawn Keirsey Jr. hit the first home run of his career in the third inning.
James McCann hit a 381-foot, three-run homer in the fifth inning.
Jordan Westburg hit a two-run single in the seventh inning.
Heston Kjerstad hit a 414-foot solo homer in the eighth inning.
Post-Match Reflections: The focus now turns to what happens next season for the Twins.
Twins president of baseball operations Derek Falvey and manager Rocco Baldelli will be back, but questions remain on the roster and elsewhere on the coaching staff and in the front office.
It's officially time for reflection after a catastrophic late-season collapse that leaves the Twins on the outside of the playoffs looking in.
